<font color="#FF0000">HOMELESS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jan 14 17:24:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all:<br>
     In regards to the Vietnam veteran homeless rate, I too have worked to help Vets down on their luck?  The question is how many homeless are real vets?  Many of those in the New York City area where I worked were fakes.  Without proof such as a discharge paper DD-214 to prove service anyone claim to be a Nam vet.  This is a injustice.  Yes, we need to help the homeless, yes we need to help vets all we can, but to claim many homeless are vets without proof is wrong and just speculation. There is no place for unresearched claims.  As a college educated professional, I have learned that claims without proof don't hold up.  Try getting help from the Veterans Administration without proof you are a vet, it doesn't work.  Unsubstantiated claims are ignorant and wrong.  To help the vet and the homeless is a necessary thing in this society, something that many people don't do.<br>
In the process, let's not make statements we know are not true.  If you disagree with me bring proof (discharges) that many homeless are vets.  
<p><code>--   (Pete) </code><p>


